The thing that struck me about it was that the $scope.displayName() function shadows itself by setting $scope.displayName again:<p><pre><code>        $scope.displayName = function () {
            if ($scope.anonymous()) {
                return;
            }
            $scope.displayName = $scope.name;
        };
</code></pre>
I have no idea how that&#x27;s related to Angular, though. It looks like it&#x27;s just bad programming practice.
